item.title: Making simple teleporting commands?
item.dc:creator: @Noob.Coder Noob.Coder
item.description:
@Noob.Coder wrote:

            if (teleblock == true) {
                sendMessage("A magical force stops you from teleporting."); //
            } else {

Put that in front of the ‘teleportToX’ and after the actual command so your actual code would be:

        } else if (command.equalsIgnoreCase("party")) {
            if (teleblock == true) {
                sendMessage("A magical force stops you from teleporting."); //
            } else {
                teleportToX = 2737;
                teleportToY = 3468;
                sendMessage("You teleport!");
        }

I think try it and if not tell me.
